---
import WizardLayout from '../../layouts/WizardLayout.astro';
import TerminalMockup from '../../components/TerminalMockup.astro';
import CopyButton from '../../components/CopyButton.tsx';

const buggyCode = `// task_queue.py — a priority task queue with a subtle bug
import threading
import heapq
import time

class TaskQueue:
    def __init__(self, max_retries=3):
        self.heap = []
        self.lock = threading.Lock()
        self.counter = 0
        self.max_retries = max_retries
        self.completed = []

    def push(self, priority, task):
        with self.lock:
            heapq.heappush(self.heap, (priority, self.counter, task))
            self.counter += 1

    def pop(self):
        with self.lock:
            if not self.heap:
                return None
            return heapq.heappop(self.heap)[2]

    def process_with_retry(self, task):
        """Retry a failed task with exponentially increasing priority."""
        attempts = 0
        while attempts < self.max_retries:
            try:
                result = task["fn"]()
                self.completed.append({"task": task["name"], "result": result})
                return result
            except Exception:
                attempts += 1
                new_priority = task["priority"] + (2 ** attempts)
                self.push(new_priority, task)
                time.sleep(0.01 * attempts)
        return None

    def drain(self):
        """Process all tasks until the queue is empty."""
        results = []
        while True:
            task = self.pop()
            if task is None:
                break
            result = self.process_with_retry(task)
            if result is not None:
                results.append(result)
        return results`;

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<WizardLayout
  title="The Exercise"
  currentStep={2}
  totalSteps={3}
  prevHref={`${base}craftsman/why`}
  nextHref={`${base}craftsman/verify`}
  nextLabel="How to verify"
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Debug this</h1>
  <p class="text-slate-400 mb-6">
    Below is a priority task queue with retry logic. It has at least two bugs
    &mdash; one causes infinite loops under specific failure patterns, the other
    is a concurrency issue. Copy the code, save it to a file, and ask Claude Code
    to find the bugs.
  </p>

  <div class="space-y-6">
    <!-- The buggy code -->
    <div class="relative">
      <TerminalMockup>
        <pre class="text-slate-300 text-xs leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto"><code>{buggyCode}</code></pre>
      </TerminalMockup>
      <div class="absolute top-2.5 right-3">
        <CopyButton text={buggyCode} client:load />
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Instructions -->
    <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/50 border border-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">The exercise</h2>
      <ol class="space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-300">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-amber-400 shrink-0 font-mono">1.</span>
          <span>Save the code above to a file:
            <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-slate-800 rounded text-slate-300">task_queue.py</code>
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-amber-400 shrink-0 font-mono">2.</span>
          <span>Open Claude Code in the same directory and ask:
            <code class="block mt-1 px-2 py-1 bg-slate-800 rounded text-amber-300">
              find the bugs in task_queue.py and explain each one
            </code>
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-amber-400 shrink-0 font-mono">3.</span>
          <span>Read the analysis. Check whether it found the real issues
            &mdash; not just surface-level style complaints.</span>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <!-- Hints (collapsed) -->
    <details class="rounded-xl bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer px-5 py-3 text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-300">
        What are the actual bugs? (verify after Claude Code responds)
      </summary>
      <div class="px-5 pb-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-400">
        <div>
          <p class="text-white font-medium">Bug 1: Infinite retry loop</p>
          <p>
            When a task fails, <code class="px-1 bg-slate-800 rounded">process_with_retry</code>
            pushes it back onto the queue with a new priority. But
            <code class="px-1 bg-slate-800 rounded">drain()</code> keeps popping and retrying,
            so a permanently-failing task gets re-queued and re-processed
            indefinitely &mdash; the retry counter resets each time
            <code class="px-1 bg-slate-800 rounded">drain</code> pops it as a "new" task.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-white font-medium">Bug 2: Shared state without locking</p>
          <p>
            <code class="px-1 bg-slate-800 rounded">self.completed</code> is appended to
            inside <code class="px-1 bg-slate-800 rounded">process_with_retry</code>
            without holding the lock. If multiple threads call
            <code class="px-1 bg-slate-800 rounded">drain()</code> concurrently, the list
            can be corrupted.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>

    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
      The point isn't whether Claude Code gets it perfectly right. It's whether
      the analysis is good enough to be useful &mdash; the kind of insight you'd
      value from a sharp colleague reviewing your code.
    </p>
  </div>
</WizardLayout>
